underlying_goal: Update outdated documentation files to warn users about their limited applicability.
primary_success: Correctly interpreted the user's intent to either archive or signpost docs, choosing the better option of adding clear deprecation banners to the files.
brief_summary: The user asked to archive or mark specific outdated documentation files (v5.1-v5.3). The agent located the files and, noting they were still useful for some context, opted to add prominent deprecation banners at the top of each file instead of archiving them. This successfully warned future readers of their outdated status for certain use cases.
